Erdemir Demir, Global Yatirim: Turkey Equity Market Preview

-- B y   A y d a n   E k s i n
-- 
2011-06-15T06:33:46Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-15/erdemir-demir-global-yatirim-turkey-equity-market-preview.html
The following stocks may be active
in Turkey. Symbols are in parentheses and prices are from the
last close.  Turkey’s benchmark  ISE National 100 index (XU100)  fell 1,337.68, or
2.1 percent, to 62,185.54 yesterday.  Eregli Demir & Celik Fabrikalari TAS (EREGL TI): Turkey’s
biggest flat steelmaker known as Erdemir, will offer additional
payments, besides regular compensation and benefits to encourage
employees to take early retirements, it said in a statement to
the bourse after the market closed yesterday. Erdemir dropped 13
kurus, or 3.2 percent, to 3.92 liras.  Global Yatirim Holding AS (GLYHO)  : The holding company
will hold an initial public offering in its broker Global Menkul
Degerler AS, known as Global Securities, on June 22-23, raising
as much as 16.5 million liras ($10 million) Dunya newspaper
reported, citing Gokhan Ozer, Global Securities chief executive
officer. The broker will offer 10 million shares, or a 25
percent stake, which should start trading on the  Istanbul Stock
Exchange  on June 27, the Istanbul-based newspaper said.  Global Yatirim declined 1 kurus, or 0.8 percent, to 1.25
liras. 